About git-sparse-checkout:
https://linuxhint.com/what-is-git-sparse-checkout/ https://git-scm.com/docs/git-sparse-checkout The general script for doing a sparse checkout is:
#!/usr/bin/env bash git_url=&#34;${git_url:?required}&#34; target_dir=&#34;${target_dir:?required}&#34; is_git_dir() { git rev-parse; } init() { mkdir -p &#34;$target_dir&#34; &amp;&amp; cd &#34;$target_dir&#34; if ! is_git_dir; then git init &amp;&amp; git remote add -f origin &#34;$git_url&#34; fi git config core.sparseCheckout true &amp;&amp; git sparse-checkout init &amp;&amp; git sparse-checkout set test &amp;&amp; git pull origin master } see also: https://about.gitlab.com/blog/2020/03/13/partial-clone-for-massive-repositories/

